      (b)  Deploy, serve, host, or publish the Frontend Application or any
           portion thereof on any infrastructure other than the Author's
           official Hosted Service;

      (c)  Distribute, sublicense, sell, lease, rent, loan, give, transfer,
           or otherwise make the Frontend Application or any portion thereof
           available to any third party in any form;

      (d)  Modify, adapt, translate, localize, or create any Derivative Work
           based on or substantially similar to the Frontend Application,
           including adapting individual components, extracting the design
           system, rebuilding the visual aesthetic, or reimplementing any
           feature or interaction pattern in a different codebase;

      (e)  Reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, decode, decrypt, or
           attempt to reconstruct or discover any proprietary algorithms,
           component logic, state management patterns, or design decisions
           embedded in compiled or minified builds of the Frontend Application;

      (f)  Use the Visual Design System, color palette, gradient language,
           component aesthetics, animation patterns, or overall look-and-feel
           of the Frontend Application as the basis for any other product's
           design, whether the intended product is commercial or non-commercial;

      (g)  Use any portion of the Frontend Application for any Commercial Use
           without a separately negotiated, fully executed written license
           agreement signed by the Author;

      (h)  Remove, alter, obscure, cover, or replace any copyright notices,
           license text, "Powered by PlanIt" attributions, or other proprietary
           markings appearing in the Frontend Application's source code, compiled
           output, user interface, or documentation;

      (i)  Use the name "PlanIt," the PlanIt logo, the PlanIt visual identity,
           or the name "Aakshat Hariharan" in connection with any product,
           service, website, social media presence, or other context in a manner
           that implies endorsement, affiliation, partnership, or sponsorship
           without the Author's explicit prior written consent;

      (j)  Misrepresent the origin of the Frontend Application or any portion
           thereof, or remove any authorship information from the source code;

      (k)  Use automated tools, web scrapers, crawlers, headless browsers, or
           any other automated means to extract, index, reproduce, or mirror
           the source code, design assets, or content of the Hosted Service at
           scale;

      (l)  Use any portion of the Frontend Application's source code in training
           datasets for machine learning models, AI systems, code generation
           models, or any automated system intended to produce similar or
           competing software;

      (m)  Frame, embed, or otherwise display the Hosted Service within another
           website or application in a way that misrepresents the origin of the
           service or removes the Author's branding;

      (n)  Circumvent, disable, remove, or bypass any technical enforcement
           mechanisms embedded in the Frontend Application, including the
           white-label license heartbeat verification system, the domain
           resolution checks, the maintenance gate, or any rate limiting or
           access control logic.

3.2   The restrictions in Section 3.1 apply to the Frontend Application in
      its entirety and equally to every individual component, file, function,
      hook, style, asset, icon, animation, color choice, or architectural
